type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

This demo wiki ships six sample profiles and matching data tiddlers.  The
fastest way to see what the tool does:

# Click <$button class="tc-btn-invisible" tooltip="Open the Console"><$action-navigate $to="$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/Console"/>{{$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/icon}}</$button> — or the matching icon in the page-controls toolbar (top-right) — to open the Console.
# Pick ''Example Reading List'' from the //Profile// dropdown.
# Open the ''Example Reading List Data'' tiddler from the sidebar, click its ''Copy text'' button, and paste into the //Source JSON// box of the Console.
# Click ''Convert''.  Eight tiddlers appear under //Staging//, none in conflict.
# Click ''Apply''.  Eight book tiddlers are written to the wiki.  An ''Imported this session'' list at the bottom of the Console lets you click through them.

Try modifying the profile next — click ''Edit'' beside the dropdown.  The
profile editor opens with the profile's records path, TiddlyWiki fields, and
custom fields shown as editable rows.  Change something, save (it's automatic),
and re-run the conversion to see the effect.
